OL,3,CAlmost 170,000 retail employees lost
OL,4,Ctheir jobs in 2024, figures reveal
OL,6,FJust under 170,000 people working in
OL,7,Fretail had their jobs axed in 2024,
OL,8,Fafter a challenging year for high
OL,9,Fstreet firms.
OL,11,FThe collapse of major chains such as
OL,12,FHomebase and Ted Baker brought a spike
OL,13,Fin job losses, according to end-of-
OL,14,Fyear figures from the Centre for
OL,15,FRetail Research.
OL,17,FIt said its latest analysis showed
OL,18,Fthat a total of 169,395 retail jobs
OL,19,Fwere lost in the 2024 calendar year to
OL,20,Fdate. This was an increase of 41.9%
OL,21,Fcompared with 2023.
